article.headline: Tesla Inc. stock outperforms market on strong trading day
article.body: Shares of Tesla Inc. TSLA, +1.89% advanced 2.73% to $425.30 Wednesday, on what proved to be an all-around favorable trading session for the stock market, with the NASDAQ Composite Index COMP, +1.39% rising 1.88% to 11,364.60 and the Dow Jones Industrial Average DJIA, +0.56% rising 1.91% to 28,303.46. Tesla Inc. closed $77.19 below its 52-week high ($502.49), which the company reached on September 1st. The stock underperformed when compared to some of its competitors Wednesday, as Ford Motor Co. F, -1.36% rose 3.58% to $7.23, General Motors Co. GM, -0.15% rose 4.01% to $31.62, and NIO Inc. ADR NIO, +0.14% rose 4.31% to $21.56. Trading volume (42.1 M) remained 31.1 million below its 50-day average volume of 73.1 M. Editor's Note: This story was auto-generated by Automated Insights using data from Dow Jones and FactSet.
